{"title_page": "Adam Garton", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n{{Infobox AFL biography\n| name = Adam Garton\n| image = \n| fullname = Adam Garton\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1962|1|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| originalteam = [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg]] ([[South Australian National Football League|SANFL]])<ref>{{cite book|last=Holmesby|first=Russell|last2=Main|first2=Jim|title=The Encyclopedia Of AFL Footballers| publisher=BAS Publishing|year=2007|isbn=978-1-920910-78-5}}</ref>\n| draftpick = No. 27, [[1986 VFL draft|1986 national draft]]<!--do not capitalise draft or national draft per 1986 AFL draft article title and the Wikipedia manual of style-->\n| height = 194&nbsp;cm\n| weight = 94&nbsp;kg\n| position = \n| statsend = 1989\n| years1 = 1982\u20131986 & 1989\n| club1 = [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg]]\n| games_goals1 = 90 (72)\n| years2 = 1987\u20131988\n| club2 = [[Brisbane Bears]]\n| games_goals2 = {{0|0}}3 {{0|0}}(1)\n| careerhighlights = \n}}\n'''Adam Garton''' (born 17 January 1962) is a former [[Australian rules football]]er who played with the [[Brisbane Bears]] in the [[Victorian Football League (1897\u20131989)|Victorian Football League]] (VFL).\n\nOriginally from [[AFL Canberra|ACT AFL]] club [[West Canberra Football Club|West Canberra]], Garton was a member of [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg's]] back to back [[South Australian National Football League]] (SANFL) premiership winning teams in 1985 and 1986.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article119474769 |title=Garton to try his luck in Brisbane. |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |date=12 January 1987 |accessdate=20 October 2014 |page=16 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref> He contributed four goals in their 1985 grand final win over [[North Adelaide Football Club|North Adelaide]].\n\nGarton joined Brisbane for their inaugural VFL season in [[1987 VFL season|1987]], having been picked up from Glenelg with the 27th selection of the [[1986 VFL Draft]]. Garton, now aged 25, made his league debut in a 103-point loss to [[Carlton Football Club|Carlton]] and during the match kicked his only VFL goal.<ref name=AFLTables>[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/A/Adam_Garton.html AFL Tables: Adam Garton]</ref>  He appeared again the following week when the Bears met the [[Sydney Swans]] at [[Carrara Stadium|Carrara]] but would have to wait until [[1988 VFL season|1988]] to play his third and final game, against [[Melbourne Football Club|Melbourne]] on the [[Melbourne Cricket Ground|MCG]].<ref name=AFLTables/>\n\nAfter leaving the Bears, Garton returned to Glenelg for one season before moving back to Queensland and has been involved with the [[Southport Australian Football Club]] as both a board member and interchange steward. Garton runs an architecture firm in Brisbane.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schwerdt |first1=Mark |title=SANFL Blow-ins 1960-1990 Part 3: Glenelg |url=https://www.footyalmanac.com.au/sanfl-blow-ins-1960-1990-part-3-glenelg-not-ready/ |website=www.footyalmanac.com.au |accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1986 VFL national draft}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garton, Adam}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Australian rules footballers from the Australian Capital Territory]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Bears players]]\n[[Category:Glenelg Football Club players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n{{Infobox AFL biography\n| name = Adam Garton\n| image = \n| fullname = Adam Garton\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1962|1|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| originalteam = [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg]] ([[South Australian National Football League|SANFL]])<ref>{{cite book|last=Holmesby|first=Russell|last2=Main|first2=Jim|title=The Encyclopedia Of AFL Footballers| publisher=BAS Publishing|year=2007|isbn=978-1-920910-78-5}}</ref>\n| draftpick = No. 27, [[1986 VFL draft|1986 national draft]]<!--do not capitalise draft or national draft per 1986 AFL draft article title and the Wikipedia manual of style-->\n| height = 194&nbsp;cm\n| weight = 94&nbsp;kg\n| position = \n| statsend = 1989\n| years1 = 1982\u20131986 & 1989\n| club1 = [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg]]\n| games_goals1 = 90 (72)\n| years2 = 1987\u20131988\n| club2 = [[Brisbane Bears]]\n| games_goals2 = 3 (1)\n| careerhighlights = \n}}\n'''Adam Garton''' (born 17 January 1962) is a former [[Australian rules football]]er who played with the [[Brisbane Bears]] in the [[Victorian Football League (1897\u20131989)|Victorian Football League]] (VFL).\n\nOriginally from [[AFL Canberra|ACT AFL]] club [[West Canberra Football Club|West Canberra]], Garton was a member of [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg's]] back to back [[South Australian National Football League]] (SANFL) premiership winning teams in 1985 and 1986.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article119474769 |title=Garton to try his luck in Brisbane. |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |date=12 January 1987 |accessdate=20 October 2014 |page=16 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref> He contributed four goals in their 1985 grand final win over [[North Adelaide Football Club|North Adelaide]].\n\nGarton joined Brisbane for their inaugural VFL season in [[1987 VFL season|1987]], having been picked up from Glenelg with the 27th selection of the [[1986 VFL Draft]]. Garton, now aged 25, made his league debut in a 103-point loss to [[Carlton Football Club|Carlton]] and during the match kicked his only VFL goal.<ref name=AFLTables>[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/A/Adam_Garton.html AFL Tables: Adam Garton]</ref>  He appeared again the following week when the Bears met the [[Sydney Swans]] at [[Carrara Stadium|Carrara]] but would have to wait until [[1988 VFL season|1988]] to play his third and final game, against [[Melbourne Football Club|Melbourne]] on the [[Melbourne Cricket Ground|MCG]].<ref name=AFLTables/>\n\nAfter leaving the Bears, Garton returned to Glenelg for one season before moving back to Queensland and has been involved with the [[Southport Australian Football Club]] as both a board member and interchange steward. Garton runs an architecture firm in Brisbane.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schwerdt |first1=Mark |title=SANFL Blow-ins 1960-1990 Part 3: Glenelg |url=https://www.footyalmanac.com.au/sanfl-blow-ins-1960-1990-part-3-glenelg-not-ready/ |website=www.footyalmanac.com.au |accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1986 VFL national draft}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garton, Adam}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Australian rules footballers from the Australian Capital Territory]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Bears players]]\n[[Category:Glenelg Football Club players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Roisterer", "label": "safe", "comment": "table", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam_Garton"}
